headline: JPMorgan ups FedEx target, places on ‘Positive Catalyst Watch’ into earnings
summary: JPMorgan raised the firm’s price target on FedEx (FDX) to $366 from $350 and keeps an Overweight rating on the shares. The firm is taking a positive stance on FedEx into the earnings release on December 19 and placed the stock on “Positive Catalyst Watch.” It sees a high probability that the FedEx Freight segment is spun off into a separate company and management reiterates the fiscal 2025 earnings outlook.
